  "title": "Network Infrastructure Engineer (Office hrs)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Network Infrastructure Engineer (Office hrs)</strong></p><p><strong>(Gov project, stable role)</strong></p><p><strong>Singaporean Only, security clearance required</strong></p><p><strong>Salary range:</strong></p><ul><li>Basic Salary + Standby Allowance + Site Allowance + Performance bonus + Other Benefits</li></ul><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct periodic inspections and audit in both software to hardware e.g. Backend IT security equipment, network switches, firewalls, servers etc to front-end devices, that ranges from Monitoring Management Systems, etc.</li><li>Conduct reviews in Security Backend System including cybersecurity requirements</li><li>Ensure contractor’s contractual obligations are met and services are delivered well</li><li>Provide accurate and regular reports to the management on performance of the service delivery</li><li>Review design documents ensuring all design aspects of the systems are addressed</li><li>Project Management inclusive of reporting of Works progress and/or Issues escalation for resolution, project scheduling/project meeting, migration or Expansion work; as well as New sub-systems deployment</li><li>RF cell planning and validation including carrying out ad-hoc radio coverage survey and reports of the Radio sub-system performance</li><li>Support review of test plans, conduct, witness of system testing and acceptance testing</li><li>Support the implementation and configurations of security and network design</li><li>Liaise and coordinate with relevant stakeholders, maintenance/project team member and vendors to address critical incidents, coordinate with resolution parties, and establish effective communication between stakeholders for post-incident reviews</li><li>Analyse third-party as well as internal processes, and create strategies for service delivery optimization.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma / Degree in Electrical and Electronics Engineering, Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>Knowledge of project management, as well as knowledge of fixed/mobile communications platform technology</li><li>Certification in CITPM, PMP or equivalent certification as a requirement</li><li>Experiences in managing and coordinating multiple vendors ensuring KPI(s) are met</li><li>Knowledge in transmission and IP transport technologies, including DWDM, carrier ethernet, TCP/IP and Software Defined WAN</li><li>Certification in CCNA, CCNP or equivalent certification as a requirement</li><li>Able to perform standby duties (based on roster)</li></ul><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><ul><li>Stable role, Government Project (Singaporean Only)</li><li>Working hours: Office Hours (Mon – Fri)</li><li>Location: Near Novena MRT</li><li>Interested applicants simply email your resume to: vincent.tan@talentlab.com.sg</li></ul><p>We regret to inform that only shortlisted applicants will be notified.</p>",
